modules.description: Generates and parses UUIDs using algorithms 3, 5, 4, 7, and 8, supporting MD5, SHA-1, random, and time-based variants. Operates on byte arrays, strings, and integers to encode and decode identifiers. Used for creating unique session tokens, generating identifiers in distributed systems, and ensuring data uniqueness across services.

The module provides functions to generate and manipulate UUIDs across versions 3, 4, 5, 7, and 8, utilizing algorithms like MD5, SHA-1, random generation, and timestamp-based methods, working with UUID values, namespaces, and timestamps. It supports parsing, serialization, and conversion between binary, formatted strings, and internal representations, enabling use cases such as distributed system unique identifier generation, name-based hashing for consistent identifiers, and time-ordered UUIDs for tracking sequential events.
